mixin gethRecipe(header)
  +gethFigure()

  if header != ""
    h2 #{header}
  h3 
    div.number 1 
    | Install and run 
    strong Geth
    | , the Command Line Interface

  p Geth is the main tool of the Frontier release. You can use it to send ether (the network’s internal fuel) to someone else, load and execute contracts, import your pre-sale wallet or make your computer into a supporting node and earn ether (ie. “mining”).

  a(href="geth").button Install Geth

  div.recipe
    h4 You'll need:
    ul
      li 
        input(type="checkbox") 
        | Know how to use a command-line interface 
      li 
        input(type="checkbox") 
        |  1-2Gb free space (for the blockchain) 
      li 
        input(type="checkbox") 
        |  Not being afraid of basic coding


mixin etherRecipe(header)
  +etherFigure

  if header != ""
    h2 #{header}
  h3
    div.number 2
    | Get some ether, the crypto-fuel of the Ethereum network
  
  p Ether is the internal fuel of Ethereum. All programs running on Ethereum need to pay the network for the resources they consume, and in turn <strong>you can volunteer to secure the network to earn this ether ("mining")</strong>.

  p Alternatively, if you participated in the presale to fund the Ethereum development, or won a reward from the Olympic or Bug Bounty programs, you will have a wallet file (.json) that can be imported and give you access to your ether.
  
  p You can also get some from a friend or purchase it online.
  
  a(href="../ether").button Get Ether
  
  div.recipe
    h4 You'll need:
    ul
      li 
        input(type="checkbox") 
        a(href="#install-geth") Geth 
      li 
        input(type="checkbox") 
        |  One of these:
        ul
          li 
            input(type="checkbox") 
            |  Computer with a modern GPU
          li 
            input(type="checkbox") 
            |  Generous friend with ether
          li 
            input(type="checkbox") 
            |  Bitcoins to exchange
          li 
            input(type="checkbox") 
            |  An ether .json wallet


